    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Taxes as a Part of Life, and Death</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Howard Tomb letter rejects Charles W Kadlec's calls for repeal of estate tax (Aug 1 Op-Ed article); cartoon</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Charles W. Kadlec would have us believe that the trouble in America is that the rich aren't rich enough (Op-Ed, Aug. 1). He longs to live in ''a land of zero death taxes.'' But if the government must collect money from somebody, why not the very rich -- after they're dead? Could any tax be more painless?</p>
        <p>HOWARD TOMB  Brooklyn, Aug. 1, 2000</p>
      </block>
